      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "LTER Ebro Delta",
      "schema:name": "LTER Ebro Delta",
      "schema:url": "http://www.lter-spain.net/portfolio-lter/delta-del-ebro/",
      "schema:description": "This important wetland is a typical river delta that combines habitats as diverse as coastal brackish and saline lagoons, marshes, sandy coastal areas and, to a lesser extent, some river islands and freshwater springs (known as “ullals”).\r\nIt constitutes the largest and most important wetland area in Catalonia and one of the most notable, in terms of extension and biodiversity, in the western Mediterranean, also having great importance for the maintenance of many fisheries in this Mediterranean region. It is of International Importance both for some of the halophilic and aquatic plant communities it houses (including a good number of rare or threatened species), as well as for the presence of endemic and/or threatened fish taxa, although the site stands out especially for its aquatic birds. that it maintains (the population of nesting waterfowl amounts to 56,000 pairs, reaching wintering figures of up to 200,000 individuals), including the presence of species as emblematic as the Audouin's Gull Larus audouinii (60-70% of the world population).",
